  <p>
      <xref outputclass="element"
            keyref="element_local_patient_identifier__extended_">LOCAL PATIENT IDENTIFIER (EXTENDED)</xref>
 is the same as attribute 
    <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_local_patient_identifier">LOCAL PATIENT IDENTIFIER</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
      <xref outputclass="element"
            keyref="element_local_patient_identifier__extended_">LOCAL PATIENT IDENTIFIER (EXTENDED)</xref>
 is used where IT systems have a 
    <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_local_patient_identifier">LOCAL PATIENT IDENTIFIER</xref>
 which is longer than 10 characters and 
    <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_local_patient_identifier">LOCAL PATIENT IDENTIFIER</xref>
 cannot be used for data submission.  </p>


